  pages    = {i--41},
  volume   = {1970},
  abstract = {A general method for estimating the unknowncoefficients in a set of linear structural equations is described. Inits most general form the method allows for both errors in equations(residuals, disturbances) and errors in variables (errors ofmeasurement, observational errors) and yields estimates ot theresidual variance-covariance matrix and the measurement errorvariances as well as estimates ot the unknown coefficients in thestructural egeitions, provided all these parameters are identitied.Two snecial cases of this general method are discussed separately.One is when there are errors in equations but no eriurs in variables.The other is when there are errors in variables but no errors inequations. The methods are applied and illustrated using artificial,
economic and psychological data.},
